The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency, NDLEA has broken silence on the arrest of Instagram comedian, Sunday Joshua Martins popularly known as Degeneral. DAILY POST reported that Degeneral was arrested on Wednesday after officials searched his residence. Degeneral, during his Instagram live tried resisting arrest but was later whisked away to an NDLEA office in Festac, Lagos State. Daily Trust reported that a spokesman of NDLEA, Femi Babafemi confirmed the arrest of Degeneral. He revealed that drugs were found in his house. “He was arrested because drugs were found in his house. A statement will be issued on the matter later,” Babafemi said.